<h2>git</h2>
<h3>Shell aliases (typed bare)</h3>
<table>
 <thead>
  <tr><th>Alias</th><th>Full command</th><th>Note</th></tr>
 </thead>
 <tbody>
  <tr><td><code>gst</code></td><td><code>git status</code></td><td>it's <code>gst</code>, not <code>gs</code> — <code>gs</code> is Ghostscript</td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>gp</code></td><td><code>git pull</code></td><td>stack override — plain oh-my-zsh makes this <em>push</em></td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>gl</code></td><td><code>git log --oneline --graph --decorate -10</code></td><td>stack override — plain oh-my-zsh makes this <em>pull</em></td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>gco</code></td><td><code>git checkout</code></td><td></td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>gf</code></td><td><code>git fetch</code></td><td></td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>gd</code></td><td><code>git diff</code></td><td></td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>ga</code></td><td><code>git add</code></td><td></td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>gb</code></td><td><code>git branch</code></td><td></td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>gcm</code></td><td><code>git checkout &lt;main branch&gt;</code></td><td>figures out main vs master</td></tr>
 </tbody>
</table>
<h3>git-config aliases (work as <code>git &lt;alias&gt;</code>, from the stack's git include)</h3>
<table>
 <thead>
  <tr><th>Alias</th><th>Full command</th></tr>
 </thead>
 <tbody>
  <tr><td><code>git st</code></td><td><code>git status</code></td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>git lg</code></td><td><code>git log --oneline --graph --decorate -10</code></td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>git lga</code></td><td><code>git log --oneline --graph --decorate --all</code></td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>git br</code></td><td><code>git branch</code></td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>git co</code></td><td><code>git checkout</code></td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>git cm</code></td><td><code>git commit</code></td></tr>
 </tbody>
</table>
<p><code>git diff</code> pages through <strong>delta</strong> (side-by-side syntax-highlighted diffs) — wired
by the same include at <code>~/.config/git/terminal-stack.gitconfig</code>.</p>
