<h2>Files &amp; disk</h2>
<table>
 <thead>
  <tr><th>Command</th><th>What it does</th></tr>
 </thead>
 <tbody>
  <tr><td><code>ls</code></td><td>aliased to <strong>eza</strong> — icons, git status, dirs first (<code>-l</code>, <code>-la</code> as usual)</td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>ls -T</code></td><td>eza tree view</td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>cat file</code></td><td>aliased to <strong>bat</strong> — syntax highlighting, line numbers</td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>df -h</code> / <code>du -sh *</code></td><td>the classics</td></tr>
 </tbody>
</table>
<hr>
<h2>Search &amp; history</h2>
<table>
 <thead>
  <tr><th>Key/Command</th><th>What it does</th></tr>
 </thead>
 <tbody>
  <tr><td><code>Ctrl-R</code></td><td>fzf fuzzy-search shell history — replaces <code>history | grep</code></td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>Ctrl-T</code></td><td>fzf fuzzy-find a file, insert its path into the command line</td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>Alt-C</code></td><td>fzf fuzzy-find a directory and cd into it</td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>ESC ESC</code></td><td>prepend <code>sudo</code> to the current/previous command (oh-my-zsh sudo plugin)</td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>rg pattern</code></td><td>ripgrep — recursive grep, fast, skips .git/node_modules</td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>curl -s … | jq .</code></td><td>pretty-print / query JSON</td></tr>
 </tbody>
</table>
